import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    total_count = data['count'].sum()
    ax = sns.barplot(x=['Total Count'], y=[total_count], palette='viridis')
    plt.title('What is the total count of trips in the dataset?', wrap=True)
    plt.axhline(total_count, color='red', linestyle='--', label=f'Total Count: {total_count:.2f}')
    plt.legend()
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    sns.barplot(x='origin', y='count', data=data, ci=None)
    plt.title('What is the most popular origin for trips?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('Origin')
    plt.ylabel('Number of Trips')
    plt.legend(title='Origin', loc='upper right', labels=data['origin'].unique())
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    sns.barplot(x='destination', y='count', data=data, ci=None)
    plt.title('What is the most popular destination for trips?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('Destination')
    plt.ylabel('Number of Trips')
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    max_count = data['count'].max()
    plt.axhline(max_count, color='r', linestyle='--', label=f'Max Count: {max_count:.2f}')
    plt.legend()
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    pivot_data = data.pivot_table(index='origin', columns='destination', values='count', aggfunc='sum')
    heatmap = sns.heatmap(pivot_data, cmap='coolwarm', annot=True, fmt='.0f')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of trips between different origins and destinations?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    average_count = data.groupby('origin')['count'].mean().reset_index()
    chart = sns.barplot(x='origin', y='count', data=average_count)
    plt.title('What is the average count of trips per origin?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('Origin')
    plt.ylabel('Average Count')
    plt.legend(title='Origins', loc='upper right', labels=average_count['origin'].unique())
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
